  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently, documentation is significantly scattered around the project. There are pieces of information in the repo, on status.im site, in CodiMD, and even Notion.\r\n\r\nAll information about the project that can be helpful to core developers and contributors should be publicly accessible and easy to find.\r\n\r\n# Information that should be added to docs:\r\n\r\n- [x]  How to add js dependency: information about nix shell should be transferred from **https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/14651.**\r\n- [x]  How to use `make test-watch-for-repl` (from #14576)\r\n- [x] Why percentages shouldn't be used for components height/width - from [discussion](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/14799#discussion_r1073742838)\r\n- [x] Documents from CodiMD that can be made public and related to `status-mobile` development should be moved to github\r\n   - [x] [Merging PRs](https://notes.status.im/mobile-pr-process)\r\n   - [x]  [Pipeline Process](https://notes.status.im/M73LlV1gT3OJ8kdSMY-ZQQ)\r\n   - [x] [How to Launch E2E](https://notes.status.im/how-to-launch-e2e)\r\n   - [x] [Component tests](https://notes.status.im/s/z7rjJu6JM)\r\n\r\n...TBD\r\n\r\n\r\n**Note: If you feel that important information is missed in the docs, or hidden in PR discussions - please mention it in the comments** ⬇️  \r\n",
